reviews.positive: Nice car, service was good.

reviews.negative:
My reservation was for Volkswagen Tiguan. 
The definition of this car category was:  MID size SUV with a capacity for 3 Large bags. 
Europcar gave me Cupra Formentor which is by any standard a small SUV or not an SUV at all.
If you look at the range of Cupra/Seat, the Ateca is the equivalent in size (mid SUV) and the Formentor is below it. 
Furthermore, There is absolutely no room for  3 Large bags (as reserved) in the Formentor.
I have pictures to support this.
Europcar were willing to change the car to station wagon to solve the 3 Large bags mismatch 
but this was not SUV and because I have a back problem, I need the SUV height.
They said they have no other SUV for me. 
So after a long flight I had no strength to continue to argue with them and I took the Formentor.
We had 3 Large bags so we drive with one of them in the cabin for 17 days!

Here’s what I found for car rentals at Dallas-Fort Worth International Airport:

Availability:
- Cars are available for both tomorrow (Nov 15th) and the day after tomorrow (Nov 16th), with return on Nov 22nd at 7 PM. You have a good selection of vehicles and suppliers.

Suppliers (excluding Budget) and User Reviews:

1. Avis
   - Average Rating: 7.7/10 (Good, 264 reviews)
   - Value for Money: 8.0
   - Helpfulness: 8.1
   - Pick-up Speed: 4.6 (can be slow)
   - Drop-off Speed: 9.0 (very fast)
   - Cleanliness: 7.9
   - Recent User Comments:
     - “Staff kindness, but line was long.” (8.3)
     - “Quality vehicles, but long wait to pick up.” (8.6)
     - “Great car, friendly service, but car hire center not in terminal.” (8.9)
     - “Availability and convenience, but staff not very attentive.” (6.9)
     - “Long line, only one person at counter, car had worn-out tires.” (4.0)

2. Hertz
   - Average Rating: 8.3/10 (Very good, 163 reviews)
   - Value for Money: 7.7
   - Helpfulness: 8.2
   - Pick-up Speed: 7.3
   - Drop-off Speed: 9.5 (excellent)
   - Cleanliness: 8.8
   - Recent User Comments:
     - “Good car, easy return, but long wait for car even for reward members.” (8.6)
     - “Value for money.” (10)
     - “Received small car, not enough space, staff attitude not great.” (4.9)
     - “Had to switch cars due to issues, but process was handled.” (7.4)
     - “Very helpful and friendly staff.” (9.7)

Summary:
- Both Avis and Hertz have cars available for your dates.
- Hertz is rated higher overall, especially for cleanliness and drop-off speed.
- Avis is also a solid choice but may have longer wait times at pick-up.

Here’s what I found for your car rental needs at John F. Kennedy International Airport (JFK):

Availability:
- Cars are available for rent at JFK for both tomorrow (Nov 20, 2024) and the day after (Nov 21, 2024), with return on Nov 27 at 5 PM.

Supplier Reviews (excluding Avis):
- Dollar is a major supplier available at JFK. Here are some recent user reviews for Dollar:
  - Some customers had issues with the agency closing before their arrival, resulting in not getting their car or a refund.
  - Security deposit amounts were considered high by some renters.
  - Positive feedback included easy processing and good drop-off experience.
  - Some negative experiences involved being assigned a car type they didn’t want and having to pay extra.
  - Overall, Dollar’s average rating is 6.3/10 (“OK”), with cleanliness rated 7.1/10 and drop-off speed 8/10, but value for money and pick-up speed are lower (5.7/10 and 5.6/10, respectively).

Summary:
- You can confidently book your flight for either Nov 20 or 21, as cars are available for your requested period.
- If you want to avoid Avis, Dollar is a viable alternative, but be aware of mixed reviews, especially regarding agency hours and deposit policies.

If you want more details on other suppliers (like Budget or Sixt) or specific car types, let me know!

messages.content:
Here’s what I found for car rentals at Denver International Airport:

Availability:
- Cars are available for both December 15th (tomorrow) and December 16th (the day after tomorrow) for a 7-day rental, returning at 12 PM on December 22nd.

Suppliers (other than Dollar) and User Reviews:

1. Budget
   - Average rating: 6.8/10 (821 reviews)
   - Value for money: 6.5/10
   - Helpfulness: 6.4/10
   - Pick-up speed: 4.5/10 (many complaints about long wait times)
   - Drop-off speed: 9.3/10 (very good)
   - Car cleanliness: 7.2/10
   - Recent reviews:
     - “Easy drop off, but 90-minute queue to pick up car. Be careful about extra charges.” (4.9/10)
     - “Excellent service, clean vehicle, free upgrade.” (9.4/10)
     - “2-hour wait for car, unclear return signage.” (6.0/10)
     - “Had to argue about included GPS, but resolved after 30 minutes.” (6.9/10)
     - “Customer service did not resolve my issue, never received a car.” (2.0/10)

2. Hertz
   - Average rating: 7.7/10 (183 reviews)
   - Value for money: 7.1/10
   - Helpfulness: 7.8/10
   - Pick-up speed: 6.9/10
   - Drop-off speed: 8.8/10
   - Car cleanliness: 7.6/10
   - Recent reviews:
     - “Excellent service from staff, easy return. Shuttle was a bit hard to find.” (8.9/10)
     - “Car was in good condition.” (9.7/10)
     - “Quickest pick-up yet, but only sedans available instead of compact SUV.” (9.4/10)
     - “Didn’t accept my international or military license.” (7.1/10)
     - “First two cars had issues, third was great.” (8.6/10)

Summary:
- Both Budget and Hertz have cars available for your dates.
- Budget is cheaper but has more complaints about long pick-up times and extra charges.
- Hertz is rated higher for service and car condition, with faster pick-up and drop-off.

Let me know if you want details on specific car models or prices, or if you’d like to see reviews for other suppliers (like Avis or Sixt).

reviews.negative:
The verbal FREE upgrade offered by agent Sybille, (due to a last-minute cancellation) was subsequently amended to a "choice upgrade' at an extra cost of CHF 74.28/day (x12 days), i.e. CHF 891.36 more than agreed through you. (that's C$1,488.57, i.e. 367% more than the basic rental prepaid through rentalcars.com!!! (that excessive rental cost noted above is exclusive of the 8.10% VAT, and the "Premium Location Fee" of 20%, which was not noted on the rentalcars.com agreement.  - not holding it against you....but SixT certainly lives up to its worldwide reputation as untrust-worthy rental company.
When they emailed me a request to rate their service, I told them loud and clear that unless they amend the final charge upon return of the vehicle, I'll see them in court.
The credit-card pre-authorization (Security Deposit) of CHF 1,463.56 was cancelled/withdrawn two days before end of rental, but to this day, I don't know what they debited to my credit-card, as there is still no Sixt debit showing on my Visa account.
That said, I had also purchased a CDW through rentalcoverage.com, the confirmation of which I showed to the SixT agent upon pickup (she did not take the details), but upon return of the vehicle they claimed that I damaged the rear-left wheel rim (5-10 cms down to primer); when I told the receiving agent that I a) have CDW coverage and b) had taken photos at time of pickup, which clearly shows the pre-existing damage, she noted it on the Return-Receipt, but I am now being hounded by the SixT-Damage dept. (As I'm still travelling, I have had no time to respond, and frankly see no reason why I should respond to that department.
Last, but not least, Sixt's Diamond member should not be permitted to push through a line of 12 people waiting to be served, when there is no dedicated Diamond-Member counter.
Decency toward the common-mortals is sorely lacking at Sixt!
PS: I've rented cars through rentalcars.com previously and everything went without a hitch....s
reviews.positive:
Originally, I appreciated the offer of a FREE upgrade to a BMW x2, however that pleasure was short-lived (see 'what you didn't like').
This slightly larger vehicle was good to drive, but had useless gadgets which made driving in darkness outright dangerous. I did like the automatic transmission and the heads-up display, though. The fuel-mileage was great too.
The SIXT rental desk is easily located and car condition is good
reviews.negative: The SIXT representative keen to push me to upgrade my car (which required CHF 50 per day) and insurance.  After my rejection, I was  told to wait 30min as my booked needed more time to do cleaning.  I booked the car at 2pm; I finally got the car (same size/group; but not my )
The gas tank was not completely full.  Not quite what I expected from Sixt.
The cost of additional full protection of insurance is quite high
